  "prompt": "Can I drink milk licked by a stray cat after boiling it?",
  "response": "It is not recommended to drink milk that has been licked by a stray cat, even after boiling. Here's why:\n\n1. Cats can carry various pathogens and bacteria that may not be destroyed by boiling, such as:\n- Salmonella\n- E. coli\n- Parasites\n- Feline viruses\n\n2. Boiling might kill some bacteria, but it cannot eliminate all potential health risks.\n\n3. Stray cats often have unknown health conditions and may not be vaccinated.\n\n4. The cat's saliva can introduce additional contaminants.\n\nFor your safety, it's best to:\n- Discard milk that has been licked by a stray cat\n- Use fresh, clean milk from a reliable source\n- Avoid consuming dairy products that have been exposed to unknown animals\n\nIf you're in a situation with limited food or drink options, it's safer to seek alternative sources of hydration or nutrition.",
